Package: BWSPsignal
Title: Bayesian Weibull Shape Parameter Tests For Signal Detection
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    c(
    person("Julia", "Dyck", , "j.dyck@uni-bielefeld.de", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Odile", "Sauzet", role = "aut")
    )
Description: This is an R package to perform Bayesian Weibull Shape Parameter (BWSP) tests developed for signal detection in pharmacovigilance to flag associations between drugs and adverse events based on time-to-event data. The BWSP test is based on the assumption of constant hazard reflected by a Weibull type distribution with shape parameters equal to one. Using data and specified prior information, the BWSP test calculates the posterior distribution and performs an HDI+ROPE test on each shape parameter leading to a decision on the presence of a signal.
